{"body": "That's weird, I thought it could be due to the refactoring/extraction, but 3-2 uses the same in databases.rake, which is confusing. Other databases such as postgresql also name it `encoding`. I think you're right, we should stick with `encoding`, since it's the correct option being generated by the application templates, but I'm wondering how it's being used all this time without being noticed =(.\n\nThanks @kennyj.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/8387946", "created_at": "2012-09-08T14:13:58Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7572#issuecomment-8387946", "updated_at": "2012-09-08T14:14:05Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 7572, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/carlosantoniodasilva", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F60b997fd68261ce70cadaf6c8226c042.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/received_events", "gravatar_id": "77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "carlosantoniodasilva", "type": "User", "id": 26328, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237fa1cbd3543c15100b598"}, "id": 8387946, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/7572"}
